<p><strong>Before your appointment:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>The attached Patient Registration Form needs to be completed prior to your appointment. You can access the form by following this link: <a href="https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/sleep-registration?first%20name=%5bFIRST_NAME%5d&amp;amp;surname=%5bLAST_NAME%5d&amp;amp;dob=%5bDOB">https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/sleep-registration?first%20name=[FIRST_NAME]&amp;amp;surname=[LAST_NAME]&amp;amp;dob=[DOB]</a></li>
<li>Please email your referral to <a href="mailto:reception@woolcock.org.au">reception@woolcock.org.au</a> prior to your appointment. Note:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li><em>A specialist referral is valid for 3 months and a GP referral is valid for 12 months. Without a valid referral at the time of your consultation/treatment, Medicare will not be able to process your claim.</em></li>
<li><em>Approval documentation from your Insurer needs to be provided in the case of a Workers&rsquo; Compensation or Third-Party Claim. If not supplied, payment will need to be made on the day by the patient. </em></li>
</ul>
<ol start="3">
<li>You will receive a confirmation SMS 72 hours before your appointment. To secure your appointment, you must SMS &lsquo;Yes&rdquo; to confirm your attendance.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p><strong>What to bring:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Medicare card/Pensioner card/Concession card/DVA card/Centrelink Health Care card</li>
<li>Test results (for example, blood tests, X-rays, scans)</li>
<li>Medication list</li>
<li>During the COVID pandemic, please ensure that you wear a mask at the clinic. This will help to ensure the safety and wellbeing of yourself and everyone you come in contact with at the clinic.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>
<p><strong>COVID-19</strong></p>
<p><strong>Have you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Been diagnosed with COVID-19?</li>
<li>Had any respiratory <a href="https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/Infectious/covid-19/Pages/frequently-asked-questions.aspx#1-4">symptomsâ€‹</a>in the last 14 days:
<ul>
<li>fever (37.5&deg; or higher)</li>
<li>cough</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>shortness of breath (difficulty breathing)</li>
<li>runny nose</li>
<li>loss of taste</li>
<li>loss of smell.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>If you have answered NO to all of the above questions, please consider your appointment confirmed. Please wear a mask when entering the clinic. Thank you for your cooperation.</p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p><strong>Payment/cancellation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Payment:</strong>The cost of your initial consultation will be between $265.00-$400.00, depending on the complexity of the consultation. If other services are required on the day, additional fees are payable. We accept EFTPOS, credit cards including AMEX without surcharge (no Diners Club), or cash. We can submit your claim to Medicare on site, given there is a valid referral and Medicare details.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cancellation or Change:</strong>&nbsp;Please provide at least 2 working days&rsquo; notice if you need to cancel or change your booking.&nbsp;This will enable a person on our waiting list to be contacted.&nbsp;If you do not provide this notice, you will be charged an out-of-pocket cancellation fee of at least $100.00.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you have any queries or require additional information, please do not hesitate in contacting us on 02 9114 0000.&nbsp;</p>
